Learning Objectives: Understand Go programming fundamentals, including syntax, data structures, concurrency, testing, and advanced topics.
Prerequisites: Basic programming concepts (variables, loops, functions).
Depth & Scope: Intermediate to advanced, covering core Go language features and practical applications.
Target Audience: Developers seeking to learn Go or enhance their Go programming skills.
Technical Details: Go installation (go version), module initialization (go mod init), basic syntax examples, concurrency patterns (goroutines, channels), testing (testing package), reflection (reflect package), standard library usage (io, net/http, encoding/json, context), generics, database interaction (database/sql, GORM), microservices architecture.
Relevant Technologies/Tools: Go programming language, standard Go libraries, GORM (optional).
Preferred Format/Length: Detailed explanations with concise examples.
